def count_possible_typos(n, S, T):

    def check(w, s):
        j = 0
        for i in range(len(s)):
            while j < len(w) and s[i] != w[j]:
                j += 1
            if j >= len(w) or s[i] != w[j]:
                return False
            j += 1
        return True
    st = []
    i = 1
    while i < n and S[i] == T[i]:
        st.append(S[i])
        i += 1
    w1 = st[:]
    w2 = st[:]
    w3 = st[:]
    w4 = st[:]
    w1.append(S[i])
    w1.append(T[i])
    w3.append(S[i])
    w3.append(T[i])
    w2.append(T[i])
    w2.append(S[i])
    w4.append(T[i])
    w4.append(S[i])
    for j in range(i + 1, n):
        w1.append(S[j])
        w2.append(T[j])
        w3.append(T[j])
        w4.append(S[j])
    res = set()
    for ww in (w1, w2, w3, w4):
        www = ''.join(ww)
        if check(www, S) and check(www, T):
            res.add(www)
    return len(res)
